## Fix #24 — `ml/src/training/trainer.py`: warning when full-resume checkpoint lacks 'optimizer' key

**Problem:**  
When `--no-resume-model-only` (full resume) was used, the code checked whether
the checkpoint contained an `"optimizer"` key. If the key was *present*,
state was restored; if `force_optimizer_reset` was set, state was skipped with
a log message. However, if the key was *absent* (e.g., user accidentally pointed
at a model-only checkpoint), there was no warning at all — the code silently
initialised a fresh optimizer, and the user never knew their full-resume
intention was ignored.

**Fix:**  
Added an `else` branch that logs a prominent `WARNING`:

```
Full resume requested (--no-resume-model-only) but the checkpoint
contains no 'optimizer' key. Fresh AdamW initialised.
Ensure your checkpoint was saved with optimizer state included.
```

